The paper deals with a computer vision problem of pain intensity regression from face images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the subjectiveness in pain intensity values, which suggests a human-computer interaction aspect, making it relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed approach involves regularization of deep networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep neural networks also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a widely-used dataset, which suggests a multimedia aspect (cs.MM).
